                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AD/12–1550: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Mission</gloss> at the United
                        Nations</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-12-15T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 15, 1950—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>591. Eyes only for Austin and Gross. ReDeptel 590.<note n="1" xml:id="d1056fn1"
                        >December 15, <ref target="#pg_1549">p. 1549</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> believes it tactically important that
                    terms cease-fire set forth reftel not be identified by Entezam comite in their
                    conversations with Chi Commies as US terms. Hence, strict secrecy shld be
                    preserved as to fact that USDel has handed these terms to Entezam comite. <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> recognizes that Entezam comite will handle
                    this problem in accordance with its own views but <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                        >USUN</gloss> shld stress with them tactical desirability of adopting terms
                    set forth reftel as its own rather than those of US.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
